en: Wyomia Tyus in her Tennessee State University uniform, 1968

Wyomia Tyus, one of the Tigerbelles of Tennessee State University, earned fame through her success in the 1964 and 1968 Olympic Games. In 1964, she won the gold medal in the 100 meters and a silver in the 4x100 meter relay. In 1968 she became the first woman to defend the 100 meter title by winning the gold medal, and also won a gold medal for the 4x100 relay.
